713481f-a.title: Manhattan: 50th Street (West) - Rockefeller Plaza
713481f-a.text:
West 50th Street, north side, east from Rockefeller Plaza. Shon
under construction between Hockefeller Plaza and Fifth Ave., is the 45-st ory
International Building, with its two 9-story Fifth Ave. Entrances. Across
the skeleton frame work appears the twin spires of St. Patrick's Cathedral
and the ornate tower of the General Electric Building.
October 19, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
